@node Glossary
@chapter Glossary

@multitable @columnfractions .15 .15 .5 .2
@headitem Term @tab Context @tab Definition @tab Chapter
@item Action
@tab Concept
@tab Statement as part of the response to a trigger event.
@tab -
@item behavior
@tab Keyword
@tab Start of the behavior section within an interface or component definition;
this keyword must be followed by @{@}.
@tab @xref{Behavior} and @xref{Component Behavior}

@item Bind
@tab Concept
@tab To associate two ports within a system section using the Dezyne
language's &lt;=&gt; operator.
@tab -

@item blocking
@tab Keyword
@tab Qualifier to indicate that the executing of the trigger is blocked till a
corresponding reply is given on the port of the trigger
@tab @xref{Blocking}

@item bool
@tab Keyword
@tab Boolean type identifier.
@tab @xref{Types and Expressions}

@item Compliance
@tab Concept
@tab Whether or not, the behavior of a component complies to the behavior
specification of the interface of each provided port.
@tab -

@item Component
@tab Concept
@tab Unit of definition and instantiation.  A component has zero or more ports.
A component has a behavior section, sysinstantiationtem section, or none.
@tab -

@item component
@tab Keyword
@tab Begins the definition of a component; this keyword must be followed by an
identifier and @{@}.
@tab @xref{Components}

@item condition
@tab Concept
@tab @code{if}.
@tab -

@item else
@tab Keyword
@tab Else part of condition statement.
@tab @xref{Identifiers}

@item enum
@tab Keyword
@tab Enumeration type definition.
@tab @xref{Types and Expressions}

@item Event
@tab Concept
@tab An event is declared as part of an interface and represents the type
of the messages communicated between components.  An event is
implemented as a function call.
@tab -

@item extern
@tab Keyword
@tab Type definition which can be used for data variables and data parameters.
Followed by an identifier and $$'s.  The part between $$'s is used in
the generated code as the type definition for these data variables and
parameters.
@tab @xref{Types and Expressions}

@item external
@tab Keyword
@tab Qualifier of a provides port definition indicating that the out events
can be possibly delayed which is taken into account during verification.
@tab @xref{External}

@item false
@tab Keyword
@tab Boolean value false.
@tab @xref{Identifiers}

@item Guard
@tab Concept
@tab A boolean expression between [ ] as prefix of a statement
@tab -

@item Hand-written
@tab Concept
@tab A hand-written component is defined as a component without a behavior or
system section in the component definition.  The implementation should
be provided in the target source language.
@tab -

@item if
@tab Keyword
@tab The @code{if} keyword is followed by a boolean expression and a statement
and optionally the keyword @code{else}; followed by a second statement
@tab @xref{Identifiers}

@item illegal
@tab Keyword
@tab @code{illegal}.  As a direct response indicates that the given event
in the given state is not allowed to be communicated.  Within a
component, the @code{illegal} is also allowed within a function or
@code{if}, indicating that the @code{illegal} should never be executed,
i.e.  comparable with @code{assert(FALSE)}; of the C-language.
@tab @xref{Illegal} and @xref{Component Illegal}

@item import
@tab Keyword
@tab The file following the import keyword is loaded and expanded at the
location of the @code{import}
@tab @xref{Identifiers}

@item in
@tab Keyword
@tab Indicates for an event of an interface that the event is an incoming event
'''or''' indicates for a data parameter of an event or function that the
value of the parameter is incoming
@tab @xref{Interfaces}

@item inevitable
@tab Keyword
@tab A trigger event that will inevitably occur provided no other events occur.
@tab @xref{Using inevitable and optional}

@item injected
@tab Keyword
@tab Qualifier of a required port to indicate that the binding of the port
occurs at a higher level in the system hierarchy.
@tab @xref{Components}

@item inout
@tab Keyword
@tab Indicates for a data parameter of an event or function that the value
of the parameter is incoming at the begin of the event or function call,
and outgoing at the end.
@tab -

@item Interface
@tab Concept
@tab An interface defines a set of events and the underlying protocol how
components communicate between each other via their ports.
@tab -

@item interface
@tab Keyword
@tab Begins the definition of an interface; this keyword must be followed by
an identifier and @{@}.
@tab @xref{Interfaces}

@item namespace
@tab Keyword
@tab -
@tab @xref{Namespaces}

@item on
@tab Keyword
@tab Identifies an @code{on} which for one or more trigger events defines the
corresponding response.
@tab @xref{Imperative Statements}

@item optional
@tab Keyword
@tab A trigger that optionally can happen.
@tab @xref{Using inevitable and optional}

@item otherwise
@tab Keyword
@tab Defines a catch-all guard which is true only if all the other guard
expressions in a list of @code{guard}s evaluate to false.
@tab @xref{Declarative Statements}

@item out
@tab Keyword
@tab Indicates for an event of an interface that the event is an outgoing event
'''or''' indicates for a data parameter of an event of function that the
value of the parameter is outgoing
@tab @xref{Interfaces}

@item Port
@tab Concept
@tab Within a component definition, a named instance of an interface.
@tab -

@item provides
@tab Keyword
@tab Used in a component to define a port and its type which the component will
provide.
@tab @xref{Ports}

@item reply
@tab Keyword
@tab Statement that defines the value that will be returned as result of the
triggering event.
@tab @xref{Imperative Statements}

@item requires
@tab Keyword
@tab Used in a component to define a port and its type which the component
will use.
@tab @xref{Ports}

@item return
@tab Keyword
@tab @code{return}; specifies the return value of a function (if any) and
exits the function.
@tab @xref{Functions}

@item Sequence view
@tab Window
@tab Message sequence chart (result of simulation or verification).
@tab -

@item State
@tab Concept
@tab A state consists of all values of a model's member variables.
@tab -

@item subint
@tab Keyword
@tab A type representing a finite sequence of integers, expressed as @{m..n@}
where m and n are integers and m &lt;= n, for example @{-2..1@}.
@tab @xref{Types and Expressions}

@item System
@tab Concept
@tab A component containing a system section.
@tab -

@item system
@tab Keyword
@tab Starts the system section of a component.  A system section consists
of two parts: instantiations of subcomponents, followed by all the
bindings among the sub-components and ports of the component.
@tab @xref{Systems}

@item Trace
@tab Concept
@tab An execution trace is a sequence of events representing a possible
execution scenario.
@tab -

@item true
@tab Keyword
@tab Boolean value true.
@tab @xref{Identifiers}

@item Type
@tab Concept
@tab An enum, subint, bool, or extern.
@tab -

@item Variable
@tab Concept
@tab Declared within a behavior section.  A member variable can be either
a state variable which can be used a part of a guard of condition or a
data variable which can be used as a parameter of events or functions
@tab -

@item Verification
@tab Concept
@tab The execution of the verification engine which verifies for interfaces
and components whether they are free of livelock, deadlock, and illegal
behavior.  Also, for a component it is verified whether a component
adheres to all the protocols (behavior) of the interfaces of the ports
of the component.  During verification, all possible execution scenarios
are considered guaranteeing a 100% coverage.
@tab -
@end multitable

